      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR OZZIE SALUTE (2) goes very well this trip starting 41 times for 14 wins and 17 minors. Missed the frame latest (30.09) when fourth over 520m at this track in a OPEN. With a clean break looks hard to beat. SILENT ASSASSIN (1) had been racing well without winning, recording six minors on end before copping a check in the run and finishing eighth in a OPEN at this track (30.20). Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. PAM KEEPING (8) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at this track (29.74) beating Another James in a Grade 5 on February 28. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from five starts. One of the better chances. ICONIC GUESS (4) was out of placings last time (30.41) at this track in a OPEN, finishing seventh and beaten 8 lengths. Has three wins already from this draw.",
